reviews.review_text: Amazing food! A group of us went and ordered a variety of dishes from appetizers to entrees. The food was all very good! Atmosphere is great too! Unfortunately our wait time was about an hour to get seated and we did not have a table. We had to sit in a line at the counter. Recommendation is to reserve a table in advanced.

We made a table reservation before we left the UK. This was our last meal in Vancouver before heading home. Given that it was a Sunday when we visited, this place was fully booked and upon arrival, we could see why. It is located by the harbour and the views out are fabulous. We had a table outside as it was a pleasant evening. Starters comprised of calamari and a Caesar salad, which we shared between us (the waiter plated up two half plates for us). For our mains we shared a seaside platter and a portion of truffle fries. We had 6 drinks over the course of the evening too. As I mentioned our wedding anniversary upon booking, we were gifted a lovely cake for dessert. Service was good given how busy they were. And the food was served hot and well presented. Total bill with taxes and grats $220, PS132

We had a good food experience in this restaurant. It s right on promenade. There tables inside and outside, live music in the evening. The service is fast and the staff is friendly. It s hard to get free table, you have to stay in a line. The food is delicious, especially seafood. We enjoyed it. Also there is a good range of different beer. IPA is delicious. The place is quite loud, clean. There is no parking lot. The prices are high.

The fish & chips that I had were so fresh and flaky & chips were great with generous portion of coleslaw.  My dear wife s burger was thick and juicy with also a generous portion of green salad.  The waitress, Sam, was extraordinary.  We will give her a 10 out of 5!

I brought my dog to Stanley Park for a walk today, and while passing by this unique-looking seafood restaurant with a harbor backdrop, I thought of buying some small dishes to take for a picnic. The restaurants staff said they usually dont do takeout, but she offered to inquire for me. Shortly after, a person who appeared to be the manager came out with a smile and asked me, What would you like to order? I ordered two appetizers, Signature Wok Squid and Fried Oysters. He also suggested that I could get a portion of steamed rice or fried rice to go along with them.I sat on a chair by the harbor and started tasting a few bites. Both the squid and oyster were very fresh, and the squid had a great flavor. Paired with white rice, it was just right. The dipping sauce for the fried oyster had a hint of orange sweetness, and it was delicious. I definitely need to go back to the restaurant, sit on that beautiful patio, and enjoy another seafood meal.

Food was incredible! We ordered the wok squid to start (in the picture) and it was a little spicy but had a nice Asian twist to the typical fried calamari you have at restaurants. My mom ordered the lamb shank and ate it all up. It was juicy and flavourful, same with my cardero salmon plank - 10/10. Pricey but worth it for a celebration of some sort!

This is my must hit spot in Vancouver. I ve never had a meal I didn t love and the servers are always outstanding.  Sit outside if you can, the views are great. I definitely recommend the fish & chips!

This is a local favourite with a beautiful waterfront view. It s usually quite busy, so be sure to book a table in advance. The service here is top notch, they are quick, attentive, and accommodating. They have been a staple for Vancouver for quite a while, so it s no surprise they are still doing well. Their appetizers are solid. Mains are a bit more expensive, but you do get a solid sized portion. Come for the view, the ambiance, and stay for a good bite and a couple of drinks. A good way to end off the day after exploring downtown Vancouver.

I was at this restaurant yesterday with family celebrating a few things. I never mentioned it while reserving online but told the hostess in conversation on our way to our table. She mentioned it to our server Nick who went above and beyond to make sure we had a good time. His service was genuinely excellent and he recommended some great dishes. Between the table we tried the garlic prawns, albacore tuna, sablefish and the feature halibut and they were all great. I unfortunately only got pictures of the dessert cause they did it up nice for us. Dessert was also really good! It was a rainy day and the sun poked out just as we started eating and a rainbow appeared for a few mins. Such was a great evening :) Thanks Cardero! Thanks Nick!

A friendly bartender and fantastic food made this a great early dinner. I had the Seaside Platter and loved it! Salmon and scallops were perfectly done, and the ribs fell right off the bone. Its definitely busy even around the start of the dinner service, so plan ahead. There are plenty of views out onto the marina and harbor, and is worth the trip.

I took my friend there who stayed at a nearby hotel. We had a fantastic time, food was good, service was excellent. I had a rack of lamb, it was grilled to perfection. Also recommend the seafood platter too. Great place to dine and entertain.

Wonderful spot to have a meal especially if you are able to sit on the patio. The view of the harbour and north shore mountains is stunning. We ordered oysters to start, a Mediterranean salad, mussels and fries and Brussels sprouts. Everything we ordered was excellent. Nice choice of local beers on tap. Service was attentive and appropriate.
Amazing food and ambiance. It was a drizzly day and we sat outside on the covered patio with the fireplace on and the rain pitter patter on the water.  Magical! Food and service were awesome!

I would give more stars if I could. Dined at Carderos last night to celebrate our engagement anniversary and the staff treated us like royalty. Incredible table right by the window with a harbour view, the service was outstanding and they even put a little candle in our dessert for us. Photos of the food do not even do it justice, everything was so tasty. Highly recommend!

The Cardero Restaurant is on the Vancouver Bay, just half block from the Westin Hotel. You need to make a reservation, or you will have to wait for some time to enter. The services a food is excellent, ending with a marvelous desert. In addition they have live music, where you can stay to hear them without needing to consume any additional drinks. Kid-friendliness: Very friendly Wheelchair accessibility: Its on a flat level to the street

Ive been with my misses for 5 years and shes always talked about this place, shes wanted to take me for so long as a treat as I usually take care of dinners and nights out. It was absolutely worth the wait. If you like seafood then definitely go to Carderos. Thanks for a memorable night and great service. So many restaurants have dropped their standards In Vancouver, Carderos raises the bar.

On Canada Day this was a treat right on the water at the marina. I thought I d stop for a snack. We split the Barada salad and the special halibut. Both were phenomenal and thoroughly enjoyed. The service outside was impeccable as well and I ll Beyonce. Thank you Kelby for a wonderful experience. We finished off with the Lemon Ice pie, which apparently Vancouver residents wait for all year! Lucky us.

Menu choices are excellent. The Sable fish dish was so delicious. Great view. Great atmosphere. Great location. Great service. Need to book for a good time tho or other wise walk in at odd meal times works too. Would 100% go bck!

Cardero s restaurant is a lovely dining spot that offers freshly grilled fish. The restaurant views of the mountains make the dine-out experience complete. The restaurant offers live music and is a great place to grab a bite and pint and enjoy live music. I enjoyed the music at Cardero s and had a great time there.

We went for a team lunch to this place. We were four people and the three of us went for the Grilled BC salmon which tasted amazing. It comes with a side of market vegetables and wok fried rice. Our server Natalie was friendly and attentive to the table. I would definitely go back to try the wok fried squid and also the fish and chips. Overall, this is a great place for seafood. They have a good selection of wines and cocktails as well.

We had a great experience with our friendly server Mark yesterday. The food were fantastic, seafood were absolutely fresh. The portions were okay, at least four of us were full. Highly recommend the Seaside Platter, definitely worth the price. Their patio is apparently popular, but if you like quite and chill space, take the indoor tables.
On the water, attention to detail, and a versatile menu with something for everyone. We had oysters on the half shell, tuna, wok fried squid, and a side of shrimp. Everything was spot on.
Can t say enough GOOD things. The best halibut ever. Fried squid was amazing.
Very nice view on the patio.  Seafood is super fresh and everything is so tasty. Service is excellent and ambience is great.  Would definitely come here again.

Came here and had the sea food platter, The Brussels, and the shrimp.. all were also delicious.  The atmosphere was perfect with a live acoustic singer who was really good as well.  It wasnt loud which was nice, just perfect that you could hear the singer and still hear your own conversation.  The waitress was very nice and quick.  And the gin drink was perfect.  Even got a free birthday dessert. Thank you!  Loved the sea food -Alberta girl

Great service and ambience! Loved the fish and chips (specials menu). The fact that they had bumbu as the rum made it even more special!! Our waiter was amazing as well with good recommendations and conversations.

Always enjoyed coming here. I always get the mussels. Good food and service. Decently priced. Great patio! I just wanted to add that I also really love the oysters. Always great and fresh. Love Carderos, never disappointed. We like to bring new people here and they always love it.
Beautiful location, friendly & accommodating staff, exquisite food and service. Definitely look forward to returning. The crab & brussel sprouts are incredible!
The food here was delicious....The Lamb was cooked and seasoned perfectly.   The raw and fried oysters were delicious .

Everything that we ordered here was amazing, other than one tiny exception. The broccolini had been left for a tad too long before they cooked it, so it wasn t fresh. The glazed sablefish was absolutely delicious, I would definitely recommend and the sauce for the mussels was super yummy as well. Their garlic bread is underwhelming, but the brownie dessert was so good. It was the perfect combination of sweet and various textures, I would come back to try something else from this place.

This is a place for a very special occasion offering great seafood in a very cool environment. Patio was great and inside is also very spacious. However you would still have to make a reservation ahead of time to make sure to have that table for tonight. Appetizers were great, and mussels sauce was a big pleasant surprise! Order one more piece of bread since you would not want this coconut sauce with special taste to go to waste! Mains were all great, as you can see in pictures, beautifully arranged and tasting great! Pork chop was very tasty. Another big pleasant surprise for a seafood restaurant. You will enjoy your visit to Cardero s !

Great lunch partaking in caesar salad, the cedar plank salmon, roasted sablefish, and carrot cake.  Nothing disappointed and the fish was cooked perfect.  Carrot cake is a must-do - so moist and great flavor.

We came.here based on Google reviews and we don t regret it. Very pleasant place and loved the food. Absolutely wonderful. Parking: Easy to find parking and not very expensive Kid-friendliness: Around us were kids, loved the attention they were getting

Used to come here a bunch back in 2013-2014. Was always a fave, and tonight didn t disappoint. The only downside was that they no longer have the amazing bread they had back in the day. Otherwise, the service and food were both top notch. Kristy Lee was a fantastic server who accommodated various dietary preferences with a smile on her face. She genuinely seems to love her job which comes through in her service. The cedar plank salmon was delicious, as were the Brussels sprouts. Can t wait to go back in the future!
A staple of Vancouver showcasing great service and perfectly cooked seafood. Always a good time here and it s always bustling!

Our waiter was awesome!  He paid special attention to how we drank our drinks (no straw, no lime) and repeated that when he refilled our drinks. The food was awesome. Would definitely eat there again.
Food was really good.  I recommend the parmasean truffle fries.  We didnt have enough room for dessert :(

Yummy dinner in a wonderful location! They were very accommodating to my 3 year old son. We came a few minutes early and they were able to get us great seats by the big windows. The services was excellent and so was the food! I had the seared tuna and it was cooked perfectly.
You should never miss this restaurant if visiting Vancouver! Great service, delicious delicious delicious food.
long weekend brunch felt extra special, the dining atmosphere was very welcoming and cozy. I was very satisfied. Cant wait to come back and try more from their menu!

Went last night for the first time, overall great experience from the moment you walk in the door. Food great & comforting, our server Travis was an awesome resource for the menu. Will definitely be looking forward to my next visit.
Went there yesterday for my girlfriends birthday, the atmosphere was amazing.  The food was great. I had half lamb chops with baked potatoes and seasonal vegetables, absolutely delicious.
Excellent service, very tasty food and I really liked the atmosphere of this place. I recommend it.

Delicious food with beautiful harbor views! We had a reservation here and were sat right away. It was a VERY busy Sunday evening, but the service was still great! The appetizers and meals came out at a good pace. Everything that we ordered tasted fabulous and fresh. If you re looking for a relaxed seafood restaurant with great outdoor ambiance, I highly recommend coming to Cardero s!

What a gem on the water! The window seat for the 4 of us was great, even with the fog and drizzle. Our attentive waiter had patience while we chatted and didnt even open the menu! Great food (order the cedar plank salmon) and wonderful ambiance!
Fantastic food . Portions are a bit small but it is delicious. The service is timely and the waiter was very friendly. The patio view is gorgeous
This was an awesome restaurant! Food was fantastic and the view is great as well. You gotta try the oysters! And the pharm fries Food
Beautiful location, along the waters! Tasteful interior decoration! Good food

Amazing food with the best view! You have to try the ribs, they fall right off the bone. And the brussel sprouts are incredible. Our server was so nice and made our experience so wonderful. We can t wait to come back someday!
Fabulous experience- fresh and delicious food, very hospitable service, and enjoyable ambiance!! Kid-friendliness: Classic meal options for kids yet very tasty and appetizing kids!

We were pleasantly surprised of the welcoming and caring experience that this restaurant provided. A group of friends and I decided to have a reunion there, and Joy (hostess) provided the best support we could have ever imagined. She went the extra mile to ensure a positive experience of the whole group. Not only she was flexible, accommodating and helpful, but checked on us while we were dining and even during check out. The food was decadent, the waitress was amazing, and the experience in general was amazing. We definitely will come back.

Great overall experience. Staff were friendly. The location is great. They even had a heated patio with blankets. Eveything we ordered was delicious and well priced. Also, the chicken fingers from the kids menu is an absolute steal. For 13$, you get an absurd amount of food for a kid.

This restaurant was recommended by both the tour guide and the Concierge at our hotel.  It was a very pleasant walk along the water front to reach.  With our reservation we were led directly to our table. (Note: easy access with my wifes walker.) A very extensive menu including a short specials list. My wife had prawns and scallops while I orders Salmon.  The food was cooked to perfection.  Service was outstanding. The noise level inside was very high. We enjoyed the meal.

What a great view of Coal Harbour! This is a spectacular spot to enjoy the fruits of the sea while dining in Vancouver. It is situated by the water, which has a lovely ambiance and fantastic vibe. Food always adequate, fresh, and well-priced, and the service is excellent. Carderos is perfect for special occasion or when you want to enjoy your day. Never hesitate to come here any time.
Service was super quick for dinner. Staff was friendly and the food was delicious! Would go again!

The experience was great! We came for dine out. The service is super friendly and checked up with us often. The food was also delicious. The crab crusted ling cod was amazing! Who wouldve thought that cream cheese and crab would make a good topping. The chocolate cake was great as well. It had a strong dark chocolate flavour. Would definitely come here again.
This is a fabulous casual spot in Coal Harbour for excellent fresh seafood, craft beer, wine and cocktails. Very nice atmosphere, beautiful harbour views with excellent service and delicious food.
Beautiful dining area. We were by the window and looked over the coal harbour. Nice drinks and beautiful food! Yum
Favorite place in the city, food was phenomenal and the service just the same. Atmosphere is incredible, try to get reservations for the patio if you can. Very special place.

AMAZING   birthday at Carderos thanks to Ronnie Teti    and our fabulous server Tymara   My favourite restaurant & patio Annual Birthday Dinner      Tye frozen lemon cake was to die for! Parking: City of Vancouver street parking is cheap!

Really fun restaurant, great view, great cocktails, and a very impressive seafood tower. Sushi grade raw fish, and really fresh oysters, clams and muscles! If they have the peach cobbler, dont think twice you wont regret it!

Had a great time at Carderos for dinner. The service by Travis made our night, super funny guy. The food was impeccable the ribs fell right off the bone, truffle fries were hot, crispy and fresh, and the bread with oil and balsamic was fluffy, soft and warm. Highly recommend we sat outside and the view was exceptional.

We had an awesome time at Carderos, the food was excellent, I had the seared tuna which was awesome. Quite a few appetizers and everything came out fast which was very nice. Sitting outside on the balcony was the way to go, I love that the restaurant is literally on the water which is a cool atmosphere. What I would keep in mind is parking which can be a hassle sometimes but there is a small parking garage nearby which doesnt cost too much money. Overall I recommend this place if you can ever get a reservation!

Carderos built over the water with simply breathtaking views of the harbour, mountains and the marina with food to match. This restaurant is very popular during the lunchtime rush, so coming a little later will give you a better experience. While busy, we enjoyed the service. The team still took the time to chat, handle our queries about wines, and move us to a window table when one became available spot-on service. The food was hearty, and we decided to share the battered fish and chips, a specialty main dish, which was delicious and tender without being too strong (so perfect for those seafood novices like hubhy). Whether you are inside or out, the views are breathtaking, and the decor fits in with the style of the building. Pricing is standard for Vancouver, based on the size of the meals you are best to share. The wine list was extensive, and we enjoyed a beautiful Monterey Pinot Noir with a 3.8 rating on Vivino.
Excellent place, food and service awesome. The view spectacular!! Its a must!!

Just finished lunch and I have to say it was one of the best, if not the best, meals I have ever had. Mark was our sever and he made the experience so enjoyable. I loved it here! Cant wait to come back

The food was great, the service was great! The location was AMAZING! We dined outside on the porch in April and the heater was warm enough that we didnt need any jackets! What I loved was, whereas other places nearby couldnt get us in without a prior reservation (not even on the bar), they just asked if we could wait 15 mins. Very busy, but worth it! Definitely going next time!

Was at Cardero s for a company event and was very impressed with their attentiveness. The server with us was extremely professional and pleasant, not to mention the food was too-notch. The creme brulee might be one of the best I ve ever had.

Cardero s is the ultimate Vancouver spot. They have a vast array of seafood options on the menu, with great views of the water and mountains   it doesn t get more Vancouver than this! We ordered the seafood platter with a couple of starters and sides; everything was incredibly fresh and delicious. I went in April where the weather could be unpredictably hot or cold; I was seated on the patio and the staff were very attentive, periodically checking in on whether we felt too hot or too cold and they would adjust the temperature of the heaters accordingly or offer blankets.

We had lunch here and our server was Katie (hopefully I spelled that correctly).  We had no reservation but from the moment we were in line the staff made us feel welcome. The menu was large enough without being overwhelming and the selection was great.  We had a couple apps a main and a few drinks. Katie was great, checked on us enough without harassing us and seem to show up at just the right moments.   The food was fantastic and certainly has us wanting to come back for more. Our 2 fave things today was the very meaty seafood chowder and the sablefish. Thanks Carderos for the amazing lunch.  Hopefully we get a chance to dine here again.
The food very tasty, the attention very good the place is nice . With very nice view. I recommend it

Peter and Toby were great servers! It seems like everyone on staff that interacted with our table had a really great sense of humour and were really upbeat. I appreciated that there were mocktails listed at the end of the drinks menu, as well as Peters suggestion to add rice to my dinner order so it would be more filling (and it was definitely filling!).
Vancouvers best in all areas: service, exquisite culinary offerings, and breathtaking views from the heated outdoor patio! Spectacular!
I love this restaurant bar vibes and definitely it s my favorite place. Amazing customer service, high quality food and fresh oysters.
The food was delicious and fresh, the ambiance is nice
Excellent food joint with nice combination of Italian and sea food choices .. attentive service and the place is right location for an evening meal

Excellent visit. Solid service by Cody. Food was amazing and my wife and I really enjoyed the mussels. She almost drank all of the soup! Pictured: Chicken wings, Truffle fries, Mussels, oysters, mojito, Caesar, heirloom tomato and burrata salad.

Had ribs as starter the sauce was beautiful. Then we had 3 mains 2 types of salmon and rigatoni all beautiful. Some how squeezed a pudding in and that too was amazing. Server and other staff were all friendly and chatty also were recomending and explaining the menu options. Also had 2 non alcoholic cocktails and 2 alcoholic ones.  Everything was perfect would recommend to anyone in Vancouver.

Went here for their Patio during Covid. Large lovely patio. They have a great outdoor heating system. Very friendly wait staff. We ordered squid, meatballs, and mussels with extra bread. Food was tasty. Mussels were delicious. Cheesecake was a little soggy. Otherwise a great meal.

Kristy was our server! Very familiar with menu and what we would like food and drink wise! Amazing timing and atmosphere was a little warm inside but I think we stayed there on a very warm day! Loved everything there but especially her service with friendly attitude! Manager on duty was also very friendly and hospitable! Must go again!

Stopped in for a drink, great atmosphere, very polished, friendly staff. Stay for some apps. Warm olives on a skillet, mushrooms again on a skillet, best of all though a property poured pint of Guinness!! My new local in Vancouver.

Dinner here for Dine Out Vancouver 2022. The best candlelight ambiance I have gone so far with a nighttime view of the harbor. Food was delish, and portions were more than enough I could take. A live acoustic guitarist/singer added a pleasant atmosphere. Washrooms were clean. Servers were polite and approachable. Curbside metered parking is available as well as underground parking on nearby buildings. Definitely will come back in summertime...

Finally made it to this location. Excellent and genuine service! Had a night snack but this restaurant is great during the day too with all its views. Mussels were good and the sauce was great. While tasty, they were all different sizes. Squid was done great. The location feels like an older ship, with all the food floorings. I liked the fireplace too. Oh and they have live music even in the middle of the week.

Friendly service and nice deck view. It was our first visit to Vancouver and we were out to a stroll when we saw Carderos and decided to stop in. The atmosphere was great and we sat on the covered, heated, deck to enjoy a beverage and some lunch. Highly recommended! (Visit on October ber 24, 2022 mid afternoon)

I had a great time at carderos restaurant. The views are incredible. Make sure you get a seat on the patio. The inside of the restaurant is beautiful, expensive rustic, and masculine. My friend and I shared the beyond meat Burger as well as truffle fries and Margarita pizza. The food was pretty good but the venue is excellent. Most of the people at this restaurant were in their 50s or older. ( You can see this in one of the pictures) Vegetarian options: This place has lots of vegetarian options. My friend and I shared the beyond meat Burger as well as Margarita pizza.

It was the perfect night at Carderos! We ordered the Dockside platter which includes: half crab   and prawns were perfectly cooked, Tuna Tataki, poke salmon, clams and mussels. Linguine Vongole with garlicky sauce was super tasty. On Sundays they have prime rib with Yorkshire, this was delightful. They also have a kids menu, we ordered the perfectly cooked Salmon. Dawna our server was lovely, friendly and went above and beyond. Thanks for making it memorable! We were celebrating our anniversary, she surprised us with a complimentary dessert with Happy Anniversary. Will definitely recommend and come back.

Outstanding food, top notch chef obviously. Best meal I had anywhere after eating a different restaurant every night over a two week stay.  I will be back.  That is if you like fine dining and fine dining portions.  This is my kind of restaurant, and the view of the waterfront is also spectacular. Food
Excellent seafood, good service, nice atmosphere and great view. I highly recommend the BC halibut.

Great restaurants with a beautiful architectural. The terrace is cover and they have a great heated system to keep you warm. The service was good. Food was great! The open kitchen concept is spectacular. I get some fresh raspberries point oyster and it was delicious. I like how the wine selection have a great amount of BC wine and have proudly Canadian product The view of the marina and the bay is beautiful.

Dined on Feb 13, 2021 to celebrate my wifes birthday & pre valentine celebration. Great food, atmosphere and excellent service & recommendations from our friendly, professional server Toby. My whole family had a great experience. Surprise birthday cake with a candle was simply superb. Thanks again Toby. We will be definitely back. Soon.

Amazing food, beautiful scenery right on the water, and great ambiance with live music! The portions are big, filling, and most importantly - delicious!! The wine menu is also extensive, and theres a nice little boardwalk area nearby for a post-dinner stroll. Its a great restaurant for a nice sit-down dinner thats classy but not too posh.

Prompt service of drinks and food (sat around 5pm). Really enjoyed the Cucumber Gin Smash! Also ordered the Tuna Tataki, Cedar Plank Salmon, and the Sablefish - all great dishes with excellent flavour! The fish was cooked to perfection; moist and tasty! For dessert we ordered the strawberry meringue ice cream; cant recall what it was called).

They had a beautiful ambience throughout the oceanfront patio, which was accompanied by fantastic drinks as well as food, and topped off with absolute superb service. Our server Kristy, as well as our manager Rob, made our anniversary extra special. Highly recommend!

You wont go wrong choosing Carderos.  Location is superb with a Window seating as the patio was full.  Atmosphere, service, quality of food is all spot on.  Delectable menu with excellent pairings for your taste buds.  Will definitely repeat on a future visit to the area. Pictured are warm olives, fresh focaccia bread for appetizers.  Fresh BC halibut for a main accompanied by rice and seasonal vegetables.   Kudos to the Chef, spot on!!!
Excellent staff, breathtaking views, top-notch dining experience. The seafood was amazing, but their pork chop was also exceptional.

Always awesome!!! This place is one of my all time favorites - not only in Vancouver, but of all times!! Its a great place to order some oysters and wine and sit outside on the back deck, to a fine dinner or just hanging out in their bar to take in some music. Ive pretty much has everything on the menu - twice, but am a huge fan of their salmon burger and curry mussels!!!

The food is fantastic, absolutely loved the salmon. Location is wonderful. Service is efficient and courteous. We had a family birthday celebration and left the place completely satisfied. Dietary restrictions: Very accommodating towards gluten free requirements, in our case we have a family member who is celiac. The staff are known and attentive and it made our dining experience excellent.

Experience I had at carderos is amazing. I love how they have singer there definitely sets the tone in the room. Going into the restaurant feels very vintage and rustic. A great spot to eat with the family or taking clients out. A grade service & A grade food. I know at these type of restaurants you dont order a burger but Im a burger guy and I had to try it. I have an Instagram page called hambao adventures and I rate their burger a 7.1/10. Overall experience I definitely come back to try different stuff.

I stopped simply for cocktails after a long walk  . So no food rating. But!! the service person helped me find the perfect cocktail...and was awesome. Would have had dinner but waiting for a friend to arrive back at our hotel  ... recommend!!

My wife and I visited Carderos for an anniversary lunch, and as always, the meal was fantastic. We sat on the patio along the rail, and enjoyed their grapefruit spritz cocktail, fresh oysters, white wine and the best cedar plank salmon I have found. For dessert, my wife had the creme brulee, and I had the peanut butter dream cake. Our server was attentive and friendly, giving us plenty of time to enjoy ourselves. Every time I am in Vancouver, visit Carderos - and every time I leave happy.
